nemacs-next TUI frontend
========================

Launch from the repository root:

  apps/nemacs-next/frontends/tui/nemacs-next-tui

The launcher starts one persistent NeLisp session with the existing bootstrap
REPL, switches an interactive terminal to raw mode, restores the terminal on
exit, and exits cleanly on stdin EOF for scripted smokes.

Key map
-------

  Printable characters   insert text
  RET                    insert newline
  DEL / Backspace        delete backward
  Left / C-b             backward-char
  Right / C-f            forward-char
  Down / C-n             next-line
  Up / C-p               previous-line
  C-/                    undo
  C-x C-f                find-file prompt
  C-x C-s                save-buffer
  C-x C-c                quit

The v1 renderer uses ANSI clear-and-redraw from the session's plain-text frame
render. It shows the viewport, modeline, echo/status messages, and positions
the terminal cursor at the session point.

Smoke
-----

  apps/nemacs-next/frontends/tui/smoke.sh

The smoke pipes a deterministic byte sequence through the frontend: find-file
on a temporary file, insert text, move left, delete backward, save, and quit.
It asserts the saved file content and that rendered output included the edited
frame.
